    "recap_headline": "Marshall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Buy Tickets Here\n|\nBox Score (PDF)\n|\nChampionship Fund\nHUNTINGTON, W.Va. \u2013\nThe Marshall University Baseball team (10-8, 2-0 SBC) clinched its opening Sun Belt Conference series with a 4-2 victory over the Georgia State Panthers on Saturday at Jack Cook Field.\n\"We got a great outing from\nDrew Harlow\n,\" Herd Baseball Head Coach\nGreg Beals\nsaid about his starter after the game. \"We had an error in the first inning that led to a run and a couple of free bases there. Other than that he really settled into the ballgame and was tough. Drew set the tempo for our ballclub. Then we did a lot of little things on the offensive side to help. We didn't bang the ball around the ballpark to score runs.\"\nThe Herd had its second straight contest with a starting pitcher registering 10 strikeouts as\nDrew Harlow\nfanned 10 in 8.0 innings. The graduate student allowed just two unearned runs on three hits and a walk for his second win of the season. Harlow recorded five 1-2-3 innings.\nTim Baird\nclosed out the game with a perfect ninth, including a pair of strikeouts, for his second save of the season.\nAt the dish,\nJack Smith\nwent 2-for-3 with three RBI with\nCooper Hinson\nalso picking up a multi-hit game.\nThe Panthers took advantage of a Marshall error and striking in the top of the first with the opening run of the game.\nMU then loaded the bases in the bottom of the fourth with\nAJ Havrilla\ndrawing a walk, Hinson hitting a single and\nOliver Service\ndrawing a walk. Then with one out, Smith tied the game at 1-1 with a sacrifice fly to score Havrilla.\nThe Herd offense broke the scoring open in the seventh. Service opened the inning with a single and was pinch ran for by\nBen Cohen\n.\nCleary Simpson\nthen reached on an error seeing both move into scoring position on the error.\nSmith then stepped up to the plate. The short stop sent a 1-1 offering to left for a two-RBI double to take a 3-1 lead.\nEvan Bottone\nadded another run with a one-out single down the right-field line to score Smith.\nGSU tallied a run on another Marshall error in the eighth, but Marshall held them off to secure the series.\n\"First of all we got the series win, that was the goal. You have 30 games in the conference schedule and every game counts. Tomorrow is another opportunity and we want to keep things flowing the way they're flowing,\" Beals said about trying for a series sweep on Sunday.\nUP NEXT\nThe Herd looks to capture a sweep as it closes out its series against Georgia State on Sunday at 1 p.m.\nTo donate to the Championship Fund for Marshall baseball, please click\nHERE\n. All proceeds go directly to the Marshall baseball team.\nPar Mar is the presenting sponsor of the 2026 Marshall baseball team. Par Mar is the official convenience store of Marshall Athletics.\nFor all the latest information about Marshall baseball, follow @herdbaseball on Twitter and Instagram.\nTo follow all Thundering Herd sports and get live stats, schedules and free live audio, download the Marshall Athletics App for iOS and Android.\n---HerdZone.com---"
